      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): index memory path in FTS text for filename queries (fixes #94102)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n`memory_search` FTS indexed only chunk body text. Queries for date-like filename stems (e.g. `2026-06-17-1649`) returned unrelated files with `textScore: 0` even when the target file was indexed and content search worked.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nInclude the memory file path in the FTS `text` column at index time (`${entry.path}\\n${chunk.text}`) so filename/date tokens participate in hybrid keyword ranking. Keyword-search snippets and lexical density scoring strip the indexed path prefix back off. Existing indexes self-heal via format versioning on `memory_search`.\n\n## User Impact\nUsers searching memory by filename or date tokens now get the correct matching file ranked first with `textScore > 0`, instead of unrelated files.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Negative control (main — no filename ranking test):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-search.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  22 passed (22)\n```\n\n**After (fix — new test passes):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-search.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  23 passed (23)\n```\n\n**All 3 memory-core test files:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-search.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.fts-only-reindex.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-reindex-state.test.ts --run\n Test Files  3 passed (3) / Tests  53 passed (53)\n```\n\n**Behavior probe — filename token query:**\n```\n$ node behavior-probe-memory-filename.mjs\n{\n  \"top\": [{ \"path\": \"memory/2026-06-17-1649.md\", \"textScore\": 0.0000039, \"score\": 1 }]\n}\n```",
